Match OS device names (/dev/sda, /dev/sdb, etc.) with SCSI generic device names
(/dev/sg0, /dev/sg1, etc.):

$ lsscsi -g
[1:0:0:0]    cd/dvd  VBOX     CD-ROM           1.0   /dev/sr0   /dev/sg0 
[2:0:0:0]    disk    ATA      VBOX HARDDISK    1.0   /dev/sda   /dev/sg1 
[3:0:0:0]    disk    ATA      VBOX HARDDISK    1.0   /dev/sdb   /dev/sg2 
